title: Celtic X-X Ross County: Mohamed Elyounoussi scores a brace in dominant Celtic display
text:
Celtic scored four goals in 10 second-half minutes in a dominant victory over Ross County to return to the top of the Scottish Premiership at Celtic Park.

Mohamed Elyounossi gave the Hoops an early lead after just minutes but they somehow failed to double that lead in a dominant first half, with County goalkeeper Ross Laidlaw making a string of saves and Richard Foster twice clearing off his own line.

Goals from Odsonne Eduoard, Calum McGregor, a Liam Fontaine own goal, James Forrest and Elyounoussi's second completed the rout for the Scottish champions, who regained top spot before Rangers' game with Hearts tomorrow.

More to follow.
